HEADWORD: Decyl
<hw>De"cyl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>decem</ets>
ten + <ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A hydrocarbon
radical, <chform>C10H21.</chform>, never existing alone, but regarded as
the characteristic constituent of a number of compounds of the paraffin
series.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

